$\circledcirc$ Bock-level Latency Predictor Design

$\multimap$ The block-level latency prediction method has been determined.

$\multimap$ The embedded structure of layer types and layer-level latency has been designed preliminarily.

$\multimap$ The training architecture of block-level latency predictor has been constructed.




Overall Progress : 5 %
Update Date : April 1, 2023

$\circledcirc$ Predictor Overall Design

$\multimap$ The first version architecture of the block-level DNN inference latency predictor has been designed. It reveals the composition of the predictor and the process of how to complete the block-level prediction.


$\circledcirc$ Layer-level Latency Predictor Design

$\multimap$ Construct inference latency model of convolution operator based on abundant real experimental data. It can predict the inference latency of convolutional operator with any Height $(H)$, Weight $(W)$, Input Channel $(C_i)$, Output Channel $(C_o)$ and frequently-used values of Kernel $(K)$ and Stride $(S)$.

$\multimap$ Construct inference models of other operators. The model can predict the inference latency of operators usually used in CNN, including Pooling, Fully connected, Batch normalization, and activation functions.


$\circledcirc$ Evaluation of Layer-level Latency Predictor

$\multimap$ Preliminarily evaluate the performance of the layer-level predictor on convolution operator under two parameter settings.
